Ebonyi State Governor, David Umahi has said the Indigenous People of Biafra (IPOB) lacks the power to issue travel ban on South-East governors, prominent politicians or public figures from the region. Speaking with State House Correspondent after a closed door meeting with President Buhari at the Presidential Villa in Abuja, Governor Umahi also dismissed the demand for an apology by IPOB, noting that it was not the governors who proscribed the group but the Federal Government.   Governor Umahi; Chairman South-East governors forum said the invasion and criminal activities of foreign herdsmen which has heightened tension in the region was discussed with Mr President while calling for joint operations of security forces to flush them out.   Our State House Correspondent, Raliat Adenekan reports that the Governor also discloses that part of discussions with the President bothers on the timeline for the completion of the closed Akanu Ibiam International airport in Enugu, request for joint interaction with the President by leaders and Governors from the region, railway to south east and to extend gas pipeline to the industrial zones of the south east